                <h1>Understanding Maryland Background Check Laws</h1>
                <p>Maryland background check laws are designed to protect the privacy and rights of individuals while ensuring safety in hiring practices. Employers must obtain written consent to conduct background checks and are required to follow guidelines from the Fair Credit Reporting Act. Penalties for non-compliance can include legal action and fines.</p>
